TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
The next few problems in this set ask you to find inverse functions and their derivatives.  You can find the derivative of the inverse function by differentiating the inverse explicitly, or by using the formula we obtained in class:
\[(f^{-1})'(x) = \frac{1}{f'(f^{-1}(x))}.\] Suit yourself!

$PAR
Find a formula for \( f^{-1}(x) \)  if : 
$BR
\( f(x) = - \frac{x}{3}+1 \) $BR

\( f^{-1}(x) \) =  \{ ans_rule(40) \}.

$BR
\( \left(f^{-1}\right)'(x) = \) \{ ans_rule(40) \}.

$BR
EOT

ANS(fun_cmp("-3x + 3", [2,3], vars=>["x"]));
ANS(fun_cmp("-3", [2,3], vars=>["x"]));

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT')); 
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD Set \( y = - \frac{x}{3} \), solve for x to
see \( x = -3y + 3 \), and set \( f^{-1}(y) = -3y + 3\), then \(
f^{-1}(x) = -3x + 3\) .

$BR Of course, 
\( \left(f^{-1}\right)'(x) = 3 \).

EOT



